      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GEM N EM NZ (8) was brave when beaten only 2.6m into third in a Waratah Final at Menangle last start. Took advantage of the ace draw for a win here two back, taking her record at this circuit and distance to two from three. May need a bit of luck negotiating a very wide starting position but finds a winnable assignment. AROMET GIRL (5) is first up since November but looks well placed here after tackling stronger races last campaign. Readied with a recent trial so look for a strong return. FOREVER ONTHE PUNT (6) was brave from this barrier last start, working but fighting well to miss by a neck as runner-up. With a touch more luck he could go one better. LITTLE SASSY BOY (3) was fourth from this barrier at his most recent appearance. Recorded a win and two placings from his other three starts this time in and strikes at 50 per cent at this distance.",
